              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MOMIX"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The gamma-ray spectrum of thermal neutron capture on",
                "58Ni was measured in the energy range of 3.7 To 9.3MeV",
                "The experiment was carried out at the tangential",
                "reactor channel. The gamma-rays were detected by Ge(Li)",
                "-NaI(Tl) pair spectrometer. The partial cross sections",
                "for several gamma-ray transitions have been calculated",
                "and by summing all of them,was determined the total",
                "thermal neutron capture cross section for 58-Ni(n,g)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Thermal neutron spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BPAIR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".-Ge(Li)and NaI(Tl) pair spectrometer consisting",
                "       of a 45.5 Cc true coaxial Ge(Li) detector which",
                "       fits into a cylindrical opening in the common",
                "       housing of 2 optically separated(5x6)inc.",
                "       Nai(Tl) crystals.-"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The determination of the efficiency curve as a function",
                "the gamma-ray energies was made experimentally, by",
                "measuring a set of gamma-rays with very well-known",
                "energy and intensity values. For this purpose was used",
                "gamma-rays from 14-N(n,g)N-15 and 35-Cl(n,g)Cl-36",
                "reactions in the region of 1.8 To 11 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
